<Author>HiIslandsGuy
<Content>Popularity Has A Price As of this writing, the Frankfurt Hilton is rated #1 by Tripadvisor reviewers. Based on its rating, I booked a stay about a month in advance. But I discovered that popularity has a price. Hotels that run very full have less flexibility to honor guests' room requests. I am a Hilton Honors member and my preferences are listed in my profile, but I also informed the hotel that I'd like a quiet no-smoking room, preferably on a higher floor away from the elevator (not unusual or difficult requests.)When I checked in, I was given a room on the first floor, right off of the main lobby and 15 footsteps to the elevator. The room was noisy and smelled of cigarette smoke. I expressed my concern to the front desk and was told that I could get a room that met my preferences for an additional Euro 25/night.I pointed out that I was a Hilton Honors member, but was told that because I was only a Silver level member, I was not eligible for an upgrade. If the front desk had done a little preplanning based on guest preferences, they could have accommodated my request without having to upgrade me. But I was told the next day that Hilton Diamond and Gold reservations are assigned rooms the day before they arrive and everyone else is assigned they day they arrive to whatever rooms are left.I am posting my experience because I think guests should be aware that unless they have very high status in Hilton Honors, their room requests may not be honored whenever this very popular hotel is running a high occupancy. If your room preferences are important to you, you would probably be happier booking into a hotel that is not so busy and has greater flexibility in assigning rooms. 
