<Content>Deserves its accolades! What an excellent hotel - it well deserves its accolades. We booked this hotel purely on the recommendations of Tripadvisor and we were not disappointed. We had a small initial hiccup in that we booked a King bedded room and were given a twin room as they were full but the overall experience made this problem fade into insignificance. The ambiance of the hotel is first class, the room (we booked an executive) was great with a big bathroom, picture windows and modern, comfortable finishes. The Executive Lounge was open plan and also first class. The staff were brilliant throughout the hotel and couldn't do enough to help their guests. I would go as far as saying I found it difficult to fault anything with this hotel, even the Executive Lounge breakfast was first rate. Frankfurt Airport is a nightmare however, so allow plenty of time. A few tips! Firstly, don't go through security until it is absolutely necessary as once through it at Terminal 1, there is nothing other than the gates except a Frankfurter stall which sells bottled water and little else. Secondly, the local train to central Frankfurt is quick and cheap. Take the S8 or S9. Depending on which terminal you arrive at, you may need to take the free bus to the station. Get a ticket before boarding to the stop Hauptwache which is two stops after main station, the travel time is about 15 minutes. Exit Hauptwache station through the exit signposted Schillerstrasse and walk straight along to the end where you take a left turn. The Hilton is there immediately on the right. Without doubt, the Hilton is an excellent choice and if we were to return to Frankfurt we would have no hesitation is returning to this hotel . It was a great overnight stay! 
