<Content>Best Hiotel in Center of City I stayed 4 nights in March 2006 at the Hilton Hotel in Frankfurt, Germany. It was my first time in Frankfurt. I also do not typically stay at Hilton Hotels as I am a Platinum Level Member with Starwood Hotels. I rate the Hilton Frankfurt as superior. Location is the best, service is outstanding from the bellboys to the front desk staff to the fitness center staff to the concierge lounge on the 11th Floor. That lounge is open all day and serves scrumptious food at breakfast and dinner, plus free alcoholic drinks. Views from each outside room in the hotel is spectacular, as is the design of the hotel itself with a huge atrium, and one side of the hotel all glass to view the Old Opera House, which is illumiinated at night. Oh, and everyone of the staff spoke English fluently. I definitely will stay at the Hilton Frankfurt again. 
