<Content>Excellent Frankfurt choice This is a very nice business hotel. It caters to Americans, and the Atrium lobby and bar are friendly places. The rooms are modern, a little on the small side, but with nice touches. Compared to the Frankfurter Hof, the Hilton is the better choice. Although the Hof's rooms can be larger(only on request) it has the air of an aging European hotel. The public areas are compartmentalized and not inviting. The staff at the Hof are formal and aloof, compared to warm and helpful at the Hilton. The Frankfurt Hilton is much nicer than any U.S. Hilton and is a good choice. 
